          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "LONGC",
                "SI",
                "NAICR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The Neutron Emission Ratio Observer",
                " (NERO) neutron long counter system and the Beta",
                "Counting Station (BCS). A stack of two Si PIN",
                "detectors and an Al degrader on a rotating holder,",
                "the Summing NaI detector."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A 35 p nA 82Se beam with an energy of 140 MeV/u",
                "was impinged on a 352 mg/cm2 beryllium target. After",
                "fragmentation, cocktail beam consisted almost",
                "entirely of 61V (24%), 62Cr (19%), 64Mn (51%), and",
                "65Fe (6%). For Beam particles were identified using",
                "the E-TOF (time of flight) method, with the energy loss",
                " taken from a 525-microm thick Si PIN detector located",
                "at the beginning of the end station, and the time of",
                "flight calculated from the time difference between an",
                "I2 scintillator at the image position of the A1900 and",
                "the PIN detector. The beam was implanted in a",
                "979-microm thick double-sided silicon strip detector",
                " (DSSD) as part of the BCS. Neutrons detected by NERO",
                "and the beta by BCS in the 200 microsec following a",
                "decay event were considered to be associated with the",
                "beta decay."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Momentum-corrected particle identification."
              ]
